New Asset listed on Blockchain -> Asset sold -> Sale Record Created

Sale_Record -> Listener -> Create new Asset Entry, use price sold as EMA, store EMA

Same asset sold again -> Listener -> Get current EMA, use sold at price to calculate new EMA, store EMA

Batch of same asset sales -> During the cacheing phase, calculate new EMA on a rolling basis


Components:
Listener Module: Polls Blockchain for all new asset sales, stores them into SaleRecord Table
Finance Module: Sweeps through new sale records and produces meaningful financial data (Exponential Moving Average) per asset class, stores this into 'AssetInfo' table 

Asset Module: Interface for managing AssetInfo in the database
Agent Module: Agentic AI Harness to interact with tools and stream responses to Chat
Tool Module: Tool schemas and wrappers that an agent can use to perform tasks
Chromia Module: Interface for querying and performing operations with the Chromia L1 Blockchain
Chat Module: Controller to interface with UI Chatbox using SSE and Agent response chunk streaming
